        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 11:55AM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1155 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
capable of producing a landspout near Monument, or 19 miles north of
Colorado Springs, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured
objects.

Locations impacted include...
Monument, Air Force Academy, Black Forest, and Gleneagle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
